-- India's NSE index rises, posts best yearly gain in five
-- By Indulal PM
-- Wed Dec 31, 2014 05:32AM EST
-- None



MUMBAI, Dec 31 (Reuters) - Indian shares rose on Wednesday, ending a record-setting year with hopes that the momentum would sustain in 2015 should the government announce additional economic reforms and the central bank start cutting interest rates.

The broader NSE index <.NSEI> gained 31.4 percent in 2014, posting its best gain since 2009 in a year marked by a series of record highs. In dollar terms, the index was the second best performer in Asia after Shanghai <.SSEC>, according to Thomson Reuters data. The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> closed 0.35 percent higher at 27,499.42. It gained 29.9 percent this year and fell 4.16 percent in December. The broader NSE index <.NSEI> added 0.42 percent at 8,282.70, but fell 3.6 percent this month.  For midday report see [ID:nL3N0UF1Y2]